  "title": "Finance Executive (Shipping)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><p>•\tManage complete sets of accounts including AR, AP, and GL<br />•\tPrepare and post journal entries, handle invoice processing, raise payment requests, and track / update receipts<br />•\tCarry out month-end, quarter-end, and year-end financial closing, including bank reconciliations<br />•\tCoordinate with internal departments to follow up and resolve outstanding balances with customers<br />•\tOversee fixed assets and maintain the fixed asset register<br />•\tSupport cash flow tracking and reporting activities<br />•\tUpload and process payment files via the bank’s e-banking platform<br />•\tPrepare audit schedules and work closely with external auditors<br />•\tCompile and submit MPA Local Business Spending reports<br />•\tEnsure proper documentation, filing, and maintenance of accounting records<br />•\tWork closely with other departments to ensure accurate accounting entries and timely reconciliations<br />•\tProvide coverage and support for team members when needed<br />•\tHandle additional IT and administrative ad-hoc tasks as assigned (including but not limited to IT system administration, answering calls, mail handling, attending to visitors/customers, serving refreshments, and managing courier services)</p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p>•\tDiploma or higher qualification in Accounting or a related discipline<br />•\tAt least 5 years of relevant experience within an accounting function<br />•\tMinimum 3 years of industry experience in the maritime sector, ideally with Ship Owners or Ship Operators<br />•\tStrong proficiency in MS Office, particularly Excel, and experience with accounting systems<br />•\tEffective communication and interpersonal skills<br />•\tA dependable team player with strong attention to detail and the ability to work independently</p>",
